  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "### Describe the feature\r\n\r\nWhen initializing a hardhat project (with `hardhat` command) using pnpm, `hardhat` will still try to use `npm` to install dependencies which may be considered an issue.\r\n\r\nBesides, `pnpm` by default wouldn't install peer dependencies unless `auto-install-peers` is [configured](https://pnpm.io/npmrc#auto-install-peers). It would be better if `hardhat` could prompt to help add those dependencies for the user if `auto-install-peers` is not enabled.\r\n\r\nWe may also need to update the docs showing how to use `pnpm` to create a hardhat project.\r\n",
