    "body": "Thanks for opening this @Hopsken. Do you mind if we make this issue explicitly about installing dependencies with pnpm during project creation? We can open a separate issue for a pnpm guide, although I'm not sure how much content that would have.\r\n\r\nWith respect to using pnpm during the project creation, I think it should be fairly easy to do? I'll leave some notes in case you or someone else wants to give it a try.\r\n\r\nWe should add a `isPnpmProject` function similar to this one:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/blob/4d7f911a53fdde847b67a6024a8ebd896278e58a/packages/hardhat-core/src/internal/cli/project-creation.ts#L429-L431\r\n\r\nAnd then use it here to generate the right params:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/blob/4d7f911a53fdde847b67a6024a8ebd896278e58a/packages/hardhat-core/src/internal/cli/project-creation.ts#L487-L500\r\n\r\nThis part of the code is not very testable, so we usually do it manually. There are some tips about testing local changes [here](https://github.com/NomicFoundation/hardhat/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md#developing-locally).",
